    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-22T11:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-22T11:44:00-05:00" n="526"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/585: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-22T16:00:00-00:44"
                            >June 22, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>202.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>There remain in Monrovia the Consul as well as Nolke and Brandt who are his
                    non-career assistants and are living with him. I urged the Secretary of State
                    again this morning to request their immediate departure but he is reluctant and
                    I fear will not take action until this Government has received assurance of
                    further protection as outlined in my telegram 198 of June 18, 5 p.m.<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d526fn67">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_380">p. 380</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
